.utm.edu/d/design.htm \"Design Arguments for the Existence of God\"] An entry in the ''[[Internet Encyclopedia of Philosophy]]'' ({{ISSN|2161-0002}}), founded by [[James Fieser]]\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20070620122151/http://www.naturalhistorymag.com/darwinanddesign.html \"Intelligent Design?\"] Special report prepared by [[Richard Milner (historian)|Richard Milner]] and Vittorio Maestro for ''[[Natural History (magazine)|Natural History]]'' magazine\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20051229165742/http://jurist.law.pitt.edu/forumy/2005/12/kitzmiller-intelligent-ruling-on.php \"Kitzmiller: An Intelligent Ruling on 'Intelligent Design'\"] by [[JURIST]] guest columnist [[Steven Gey|Stephen G. Gey]], December 29, 2005\n*[https://www.aclu.org/files/images/asset_upload_file577_23137.pdf ''Kitzmiller v. Dover Area School District''] (PDF) A 139-page in-depth opinion of intelligent design, irreducible complexity, and the book ''[[Of Pandas and People]]'' by U.S. District Judge [[John E. Jones III]]\n* {{cite book |author=National Academy of Sciences |authorlink=National Academy of Sciences |year=1999 |title=Science and Creationism: A View from the National Academy of Sciences |url=https://archive.org/details/sciencecreationi0000unse |edition=2nd |location=Washington, D.C. |publisher=[[National Academy Press]] |isbn=978-0-309-06406-4 |lccn=99006259 |oclc=43803228 |ref=National Academy of Sciences 1999 |doi=10.17226/6024 |pmid=25101403 |url-access=registration }}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20140121215501/http://old.richarddawkins.net/articles/129-natural-39-knowledge-39-and-natural-39-design-39 \"Natural 'Knowledge' and Natural 'Design'\"] by [[Richard Dawkins]], May 15, 2006\n*[http://www.talkorigins.org/ TalkOrigins Archive] Archive of the Usenet discussion group [[talk.origins]]\n*[http://www.texscience.org/ Texas Citizens for Science]\n*[http://ncse.com/creationism/general/what-is-intelligent-design-creationism \"What Is Intelligent Design Creationism?\"] Nationa