14dran(Gakuran)|\u6d0b\u30e9\u30f3\uff08\u5b66\u30e9\u30f3\uff09}}\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=http://iss.ndl.go.jp/books/R100000002-I000011279464-00|script-title=ja:\u30de\u30b8\u3059\u304b\u5b66\u57122 1 |accessdate=2015-06-08 |publisher=National Diet Library |language=Japanese}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2012\n| {{Nihongo|Counter no Futari season 2(episode 11)|\u30ab\u30a6\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc\u306e\u3075\u305f\u308a \u30b7\u30fc\u30ba\u30f32}}\n| Young mother\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.twellv.co.jp/event/counter2/lineup/11.html|script-title=ja:\u30ab\u30a6\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc\u306e\u3075\u305f\u308a #11\u300c\u771f\u591c\u4e2d\u306e\u679c\u5b9f\u300d |accessdate=2015-06-08 |publisher=World Hi-Vision Channel, Inc. |language=Japanese}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2013\n| {{Nihongo|[[Detarame Hero]] (episode 6)|\u3067\u305f\u3089\u3081\u30d2\u30fc\u30ed\u30fc}}\n| Moe Hoshino\n| <ref>{{cite web |url=http://japan.techinsight.jp/2013/04/miyazawasae-drama-hero20130421.html|script-title=ja:\u3010\u30a8\u30f3\u30bf\u304c\u30d3\u30bf\u30df\u30f3\u266a\u3011\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u304c\u30c9\u30e9\u30de\u300e\u3067\u305f\u3089\u3081\u30d2\u30fc\u30ed\u30fc\u300f\u306b\u51fa\u6f14\u6c7a\u5b9a\u3002\u64ae\u5f71\u524d\u306f\u7dca\u5f35\u3067\u7720\u308c\u305a\u3002 |accessdate=2015-06-08 |publisher=Mediaproductsjapan Co,Ltd. |language=Japanese}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2014\n| {{Nihongo| Dr. Nurse Aid|Dr.\u30ca\u30fc\u30b9\u30a8\u30a4\u30c9}}\n| Nurse\n| <ref>{{cite web |title=[86\u56de]\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u3001SP\u30c9\u30e9\u30de\u300eDr.\u30ca\u30fc\u30b9\u30a8\u30a4\u30c9\u300f\u306b\u51fa\u6f14!\u300c\u79c1\u304c\u3053\u306e1\u5e74\u3067\u611f\u3058\u305f\u300eLOVE\u3058\u3083\u306a\u304f\u3066\"\u3084\u3055\u3057\u3055\u3067\u3001\u3067\u304d\u3066\u3044\u304f\u611b\"\u300f\u304c\u4f1d\u308f\u308b\u30c9\u30e9\u30de\u300d|url=http://ure.pia.co.jp/articles/-/27212|accessdate=2017-01-06 |publisher=TV Asahi |language=Japanese|date=2014-11-07}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2016\n| {{Nihongo| Ossan's Love|\u304a\u3063\u3055\u3093\u305a\u30e9\u30d6}}\n| Minato Asuka\n| <ref name=\"PIA Corporation\"/>\n|}\n\n=== Television (Excerpts) ===\n\nAside of numerous appearances in most of the group's house shows (most notably [[:ja:AKBINGO!|AKBingo!]], {{Nihongo|AKB48 Nemousu TV|AKB48\u30cd\u7533\u30c6\u30ec\u30d3}}, {{Nihongo|Shukan AKB48|\u9031\u520aAKB}},\n[[:ja:AKB\u3068\u00d7\u00d7!|AKB to \u00d7\u00d7!]], [[:ja:SKE48 \u30a8\u30d3\u30b7\u30e7\u30fc!|SKE48 Ebisho!]], or [[:ja:SKE48 \u30a8\u30d3\u30ab\u30eb\u30c1\u30e7!|SKE48 EbiCalcio]]), Miyazawa is also frequently appearing  in [[Japanese variety show]]s.\nThe following non-exhaustive list includes shows she recurrently appeared in and otherwise notable shows, both as a [[Tarento]] or representing the group.\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Station\n|-\n| 2010\n| {{nihongo|G.I. Goro|G\uff0eI\uff0e\u30b4\u30ed\u30fc}}\n| [[Tokyo Broadcasting System|TBS]]\n|-\n| 2010\n| [[Quiz! Hexagon II]]\n| [[Fuji TV]]\n|-\n| 2010\n| [[:ja:\u5bc6\u5ba4\u8b0e\u89e3\u304d\u30d0\u30e9\u30a8\u30c6\u30a3\u30fc \u8131\u51fa\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0DERO!|DERO!]]\n| [[Nippon TV]]\n|-\n| 2011, 2015\n| [[Mecha-Mecha Iketeru!]]\n| Fuji TV\n|-\n| 2011\n| [[SMAPxSMAP]]\n| Fuji TV\n|-\n| 2011-2012\n| [[Waratte Iitomo!]]\n| Fuji TV\n|-\n|2011-2012\n| {{nihongo|Bakush\u014d! Dai-Nippon Akan Keisatsu|\u7206\u7b11\uff01\u5927\u65e5\u672c\u30a2\u30ab\u30f3\u8b66\u5bdf}}\n| Fuji TV\n|-\n| 2012\n| [[:ja:\u306a\u307e\u3046\u307e|Namauma]]\n| Fuji TV\n|-\n| 2012\n| [[:ja:run for money \u9003\u8d70\u4e2d|Tosochu - Run for money!]]\n| Fuji TV\n|-\n| 2013\n| [[:ja:\u30cd\u30d7\u30ea\u30fc\u30b0|NEP league]]\n| Fuji TV\n|-\n| 2013\n| [[:ja:\u4e16\u754c\u306e\u6751\u3067\u767a\u898b!\u3053\u3093\u306a\u3068\u3053\u308d\u306b\u65e5\u672c\u4eba|Sekai no Mura de Hakken! Konna Tokoro ni Nihonjin]]\n| [[TV Asahi]]\n|-\n| 2013 - 2014\n| {{nihongo|Umazuki!|\u3046\u307e\u30ba\u30ad\u30c3}}\n| Fuji TV\n|-\n| 2014\n| [[:ja:\u8da3\u5473\u306e\u5712\u82b8 \u3084\u3055\u3044\u306e\u6642\u9593|Shumi no engei ya sai no jikan]]\n| [[NHK Educational TV]]\n|-\n|-\n| 2015\n| [[:ja:\u308f\u304c\u307e\u307e!\u6c17\u307e\u307e!\u65c5\u6c17\u5206|Wagamama! Kimama! Tabi kibun]]\n| Fuji TV\n|-\n| 2013, 2016\n| [[:ja:Shibuya Deep A|Shibuya Deep A!]]\n| [[NHK]]\n|-\n| 2016\n| [[:ja:\u30d2\u30eb\u30ca\u30f3\u30c7\u30b9!|Hirunandesu!]]\n| Nippon TV\n|-\n| 2016\n| [[:ja:\u30ed\u30fc\u30ab\u30eb\u8def\u7dda\u30d0\u30b9\u4e57\u308a\u7d99\u304e\u306e\u65c5|R\u00f4karu rosen basu noritsugi no tabi]].\n| [[TV Tokyo]]\n|}\n\n== Radio ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role\n|-\n| 2007-\n| {{Nihongo|ON8 \"Hashira Night! with AKB48!|ON8\u300c\u67f1NIGHT! with AKB48\u300d}}\n| Self\n|-\n| 2007-\n| {{Nihongo|AKB48 Asu made mou chotto.|AKB48 \u660e\u65e5\u307e\u3067\u3082\u3046\u3061\u3087\u3063\u3068\u3002}}\n| Self\n|-\n| 2010-\n| [[:ja:AKB48\u306e\u30aa\u30fc\u30eb\u30ca\u30a4\u30c8\u30cb\u30c3\u30dd\u30f3|AKB48 no Allnight Nippon]]\n| Self\n|-\n| 2010\u20132013\n| [[:ja:\u30ea\u30c3\u30b9\u30f3? \u301cLive 4 Life\u301c|Listen (Live 4 Life)]]\n| Self (Solo MC in June & November 2010, double MC in April 2013)\n|-\n| 2010\u2013\n| [[:ja:AKB48\u79cb\u5143\u624d\u52a0\u30fb\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u306e\u3046\u3063\u304b\u308a\u30c1\u30e3\u30f3\u30cd\u30eb|AKB48 Akimoto Sayaka\u00b7Miyazawa Sae no Ukkari Channel]]\n| Self (co-hostess)\n|-\n| 2011\n| [[:ja:AKB48\u306e\"\u79c1\u305f\u3061\u306e\u7269\u8a9e\"|AKB48 no \"Watashi tachi no Monogatari\"]]\n| Self\n|-\n| 2012\u20132013\n| ViVADiVA\n| Self (co-hostess)\n|}\n\n== Other stage performances ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Title !! Role\n|-\n| 2009\n| {{Nihongo|AKB48 Kagekidan \"Infinity\"|AKB\u6b4c\u5287\u56e3\u300c\u221e\u30fbInfinity\u300d}}\n| {{Nihongo|Ruka Murasame|\u6751\u96e8\u30eb\u30ab}} (Leading actress, double cast with [[Sayaka Akimoto]])\n|-\n| 2010\n| {{Nihongo|Space Wars Replay|\u30b9\u30da\u30fc\u30b9\u30fb\u30a6\u30a9\u30fc\u30ba\u518d\u6f14}}\n|\n|-\n| 2011\n| {{Nihongo|Double Heroine|\u30b9\u30fc\u30d1\u30fcLIVE\u30b7\u30e7\u30fc\u300c\u30c0\u30d6\u30eb\u30d2\u30ed\u30a4\u30f3\u300d}}\n| Asuka Mizutani\n|-\n| 2013\n| {{Nihongo|Wings of Kuzariana|\u30af\u30b6\u30ea\u30a2\u30fc\u30ca\u306e\u7ffc}}\n| Koruri\n|-\n| 2014\n| {{Nihongo|AKB49 Ren'ai kinshi j\u014drei|AKB49\u301c\u604b\u611b\u7981\u6b62\u6761\u4f8b}}\n| Minoru Urayama (Leading male role)\n|-\n| 2016\n| {{nihongo|Crest of the Royal Family|\u738b\u5bb6\u306e\u7d0b\u7ae0|\u014cke no Monsh\u014d}}\n| Carol (Leading female role)\n|-\n| 2017 (8 April to 31 May)\n| {{nihongo|Crest of the Royal Family Replay |\u738b\u5bb6\u306e\u7d0b\u7ae0\u518d\u6f14|\u014cke no Monsh\u014d}}\n| Carol (Leading female role)\n|-\n| 2017 (24 July to 3 August)\n| {{nihongo|Peter Pan |\u30d4\u30fc\u30bf\u30fc\u30fb\u30d1\u30f3}}\n| Tiger Lily\n|-\n| 2017 (29 September to 8 October)\n| {{nihongo|TOKYO TRIBE |TOKYO TRIBE}}\n| Sunmi\n|-\n| 2017 (27 November to 20 December)\n| {{nihongo|YUMING x Imperial Threater Vol. 3 Asahi no Naka de Hohoende |\u30e6\u30fc\u30df\u30f3\u00d7\u5e1d\u5287 vol.3 \u671d\u967d\u306e\u4e2d\u3067\u5fae\u7b11\u3093\u3067}}\n| Sara Kitaoka \u5317\u5ca1\u7d17\u826f (Leading female role) / Emi\uff08\u6075\u7f8e\uff09\n|-\n| 2018 (March to May)\n| {{nihongo2|ZEROTOPIA}}\n| Sandy\n|-\n| 2019 (22 July to August)\n| {{nihongo|Peter Pan |\u30d4\u30fc\u30bf\u30fc\u30fb\u30d1\u30f3}}\n| Tiger Lily\n|-\n|}\n\n==Bibliography==\n\n===Magazines===\n* ''Samurai ELO'', Inforest (January 2011-December 2013)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://flave.co.jp/pages/talent/miyazawa_sae/media |title=Sae Miyazawa agent profile |accessdate=2015-06-08 |publisher=Flave Entertainment |language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\n===Photobooks===\n* ''Kanojo'' ([[Kodansha]], 21 August 2009) {{ISBN|9784062156967}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://iss.ndl.go.jp/books/R100000002-I000010547448-00|script-title=ja:\u5f7c\u5973:AKB 48\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u30d5\u30a1\u30fc\u30b9\u30c8\u5199\u771f\u96c6 |accessdate=2015-06-08 |publisher=National Diet Library |language=Japanese}}</ref>\n* ''Namida no Yukue'' ([[Wani Books]], 16 February 2015) {{ISBN|9784847046889}}<ref>{{cite web |url=http://iss.ndl.go.jp/books/R100000002-I026079923-00|script-title=ja:\u6d99\u306e\u884c\u65b9:\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u30d5\u30a9\u30c8\u30d6\u30c3\u30af |accessdate=2015-06-08 |publisher=National Diet Library |language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n* [http://flave.co.jp/pages/talent/miyazawa_sae/index Flave Entertainment Profile] {{in lang|ja}}\n* [http://ameblo.jp/miyazawafamily/ Official blog] {{in lang|ja}}\n* {{Twitter|name=Official Twitter Account}} {{in lang|ja}}\n* [http://miyazawasae.jp/ Official web presence] {{in lang|ja}}\n\n{{AKB48}}\n{{SKE48}}\n{{SNH48}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Miyazawa, Sae}}\n[[Category:1990 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Singers from Tokyo]]\n[[Category:Japanese idols]]\n[[Category:AKB48 members]]\n[[Category:SNH48 members]]\n[[Category:Mandarin-language singers]]\n[[Category:Japanese female pop singers]]\n[[Category:Japanese actresses]]\n[[Category:21st-century women singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Japanese singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century Japanese actresses]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox musical artist\n| name                = Sae Miyazawa\n| image               = \n| caption             = \n| background          = solo_singer\n| native_name         = \u5bae\u6fa4 \u4f50\u6c5f\n| native_name_lang    = ja\n| alias               = Sae-chan (\u3055\u3048\u3061\u3083\u3093), Genking (\u30b2\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0)\n| birth_date          = {{Birth date and age|1990|8|13|df=y}}\n| origin              = Tokyo, Japan\n| genre               = [[J-pop]]\n| occupation          = {{flatlist| \n* [[Japanese idol]]\n* singer\n* actress}}\n| years_active        = 2006-present\n| label               = [[King Records (Japan)|You, Be Cool! / King]], [[avex]]\n| associated_acts     = {{flatlist| \n* [[AKB48]]\n* [[SNH48]]\n* [[SKE48]]\n* [[Chocolove from AKB48]]\n* [[Diva (Japanese band)|Diva]]}}\n}}\n\n{{Nihongo|'''Sae Miyazawa'''|\u5bae\u6fa4 \u4f50\u6c5f|Miyazawa Sae|born August 13, 1990 in Tokyo}} is a singer, actress, [[tarento]] and former [[Japanese idol]], best known for her affiliations with [[AKB48]] and its various sister- and subgroups.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/prof/444113/profile/|script-title=ja:\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u306e\u30d7\u30ed\u30d5\u30a3\u30fc\u30eb|trans-title=Sae Miyazawa's Profile |accessdate=2015-06-08 |publisher=oricon ME inc. |language=Japanese}}</ref> Between 2006 and 2016, she was a part of the promoting line up of 33 AKB48 and 4 [[SKE48]] single releases.\n\n==Music career==\n\n===2006\u20132012: AKB48===\nAfter being rejected during the first audition for [[AKB48]], Miyazawa auditioned again in February 2006 in an applicant pool of about twelve thousand aspiring idols. This time, she was selected as one of the 19 girls for AKB48's newly created Team K, which made its stage debut on April 1, 2006.<ref name=\"AKBINGO!\">{{Cite episode |title=AKBINGO! |url=http://www.ntv.co.jp/AKBINGO/ |network=[[Nippon Television]] |location=Japan |airdate=2010-07-14}}</ref> She stayed with Team K and AKB48 until August 2012.\n\nDuring this period, Miyazawa participated in the title tracks of 25 of the 27 AKB48 single releases, missing only the A-sides of \"[[Chance no Junban]]\" and \"[[Ue kara Mariko]]\", for which the featured members were determined by a [[rock-paper-scissors]]-tournament. In October 2011, she was named the AKB48 member with the most appearances in the popular music show ''Music Japan'' on [[NHK]], with 34 performances.<ref name=\"Music Japan\">{{Cite episode |title=MJ presents AKB48 Request Special 2011 ~Kamikyoku Matsuri~ |url=http://www.nhk.or.jp/mj/index.html |network=[[NHK]] |location=[[Japan]] |airdate=2011-11-15}}</ref> Although this underlines her role as one of the promotional fixtures of the group at that time, she did not reach the popularity level of fellow members like [[Atsuko Maeda]] or [[Oshima Yuko]]. Within her time in the group, she became a member of two AKB48 side projects: [[Chocolove from AKB48]] was established in 2007 as a trio with fellow AKB48 members [[Sayaka Akimoto]] and Rina Nakanishi. The group released two singles and an album, but disbanded in 2008 following Nakanishi's departure from AKB48. In 2011, AKB48 announced that she and Akimoto would be part of another spin-off called [[Diva (Japanese band)|Diva]], along with [[Ayaka Umeda]] and [[Yuka Masuda]]. Following the departure of Akimoto and Masuda, Diva was disbanded in late 2014, after releasing a farewell single and album.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2014/08/akb48s-sub-unit-diva-to-disband-within-the-year |title=AKB48's sub-unit DiVA to disband within the year |publisher=tokyohive.com |date=2014-08-14 |accessdate=2014-08-15}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2011, an exhibition of her self-portraits was held at the AKB48 Official Shop in Hong Kong,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ameblo.jp/akb48-hk/entry-10779526743.html |title=Sae Miyazawa Photo Exhibition being held(AKB48 Museum in Hong Kong) |work=AKB48 Official Shop Hong Kong Official Blog |language=Japanese |date=2011-01-25}}</ref> She then visited Hong Kong on January 28, and attended a series of events, including an AKB48 Cosplay Event held in [[Dragon Centre]] in [[Kowloon]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ameblo.jp/akb48-hk/entry-10779298453.html |trans-title=Notice of shake-hand with Sae Miyazawa & AKB48 Performance Award Hong Kong 2011 |title=\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u63e1\u624b\u4f1a\u3068AKB48\u30d1\u30d5\u30a9\u30fc\u30de\u30f3\u30b9\u5927\u8cde\u9999\u6e2f2011\u958b\u50ac\u306e\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b |work=AKB48 Official Shop Hong Kong Official Blog |date=2011-01-25 |language=Japanese}}</ref> In March 2012, during AKB48's trip to the [[National Cherry Blossom Festival]], Miyazawa visited the Strong John Thomson Elementary School in [[Washington, D.C.]], to explain Japanese pop culture to the pupils.<ref>{{cite news |last=Hesse |first=Monica |url=https://articles.washingtonpost.com/2012-03-27/lifestyle/35448205_1_akb48-manga-japanese-press |title=Japanese girl group AKB48 breezes through D.C. in whirlwind of cuteness |newspaper=[[The Washington Post]] |date=2012-03-27 |access-date=2013-09-25 |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928065922/http://articles.washingtonpost.com/2012-03-27/lifestyle/35448205_1_akb48-manga-japanese-press |archive-date=2013-09-28 }}</ref>\n\n===2012\u20132015: SNH48 and SKE48===\nIn August 2012, it was announced that Miyazawa and fellow AKB48 member Mariya Suzuki would be transferred overseas to help lead [[Shanghai]]-based sister group [[SNH48]].<ref>{{cite web |first=Tommy |last=Kono |url=http://www.akb48wrapup.com/2012/08/miyazawa-takajo-will-be-transferred-overseas-akb48-has-announced-new-reformation-group-reshuffle-at-the-first-day-of-their-dream-stage/ |title=Miyazawa & Takajo will be transferred overseas! \u2022 AKB48WrapUp |publisher=Akb48wrapup.com |date= |accessdate=2013-09-25}}</ref><ref name=\"struggling\" /> This transfer was initially scheduled to last six to twelve months, while the affected members were still affiliated with AKB48, as \"Team Abroad\" (\u6d77\u5916, kaigai).<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tokyohive.com/2012/09/akb48-theater-manager-togasaki-tomonobu-comments-on-miyazawa-sae-takajo-akis-transfers-overseas/ |title=AKB48 Theater manager Togasaki Tomonobu comments on Miyazawa Sae & Takajo Aki's transfers overseas |work=Tokyohive |date=2012-09-03 |accessdate=2013-09-25}}</ref> Because she and Suzuki did not have working visas for China, they rarely appeared with SNH48; for instance, they only appeared as audience members for the group's first public performance.<ref name=\"struggling\">{{cite web |first=Tommy |last=Kono |url=http://www.akb48wrapup.com/2013/02/in-shanghai-miyazawa-sae-struggling-to-lead-an-immature-snh48-members/ |title=In Shanghai, Miyazawa Sae struggling to lead immature SNH48 members \u2022 AKB48WrapUp |publisher=Akb48wrapup.com |date=2013-02-21 |accessdate=2013-09-25}}</ref> They however did appear together as group representatives at the Japanese Night at the Summer Davos in [[Tianjin]], China, and were mentioned in the official diary of the Japanese prime minister.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://dwl.gov-online.go.jp/video/cao/dl/public_html/gov/pdf/hlj/20121001/04.pdf |title=Prime Minister's Diary |language=English |publisher=dwl.gov-online.go.jp |date=2012-10-01 |accessdate=2016-08-07}}</ref> During the opening ceremony of SNH48's theater in Shanghai in September 2013, group officials announced that Miyazawa would begin to perform with the group on October 11, 2013.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ameblo.jp/miyazawafamily/entry-11605459769.html |title=SNH48\u5287\u5834\u30fc\uff01\uff01\uff5c\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u30aa\u30d5\u30a3\u30b7\u30e3\u30eb\u30d6\u30ed\u30b0\u300c\u304a\u3084\u3059\u307f\u306a\u3055\u3048\u300d |language=Japanese |publisher=Ameblo.jp |date=2013-09-02 |accessdate=2013-09-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2013/09/29/kiji/K20130929006715410.html |script-title=ja:\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u3089\uff33\uff2e\uff28\uff14\uff18\u5287\u5834\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u6c7a\u5b9a\u300c\u3084\u3063\u305f\u3041\u30fc\uff01 |language=Japanese |publisher=sponichi.co.jp |date=2013-09-29 |accessdate=2013-09-29}}</ref> Indeed, both Miyazawa and Suzuki debuted with SNH48 on that date, triggering media coverage in both Japan<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/akb48/news/p-et-tp0-20131012-1202933.html |script-title=ja:\uff33\uff2e\uff2848\u5bae\u6ca2\uff06\u9234\u6728\u304c\u4e0a\u6d77\u5287\u5834\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc |language=Japanese |publisher=nikkansports.com |date=2013-10-12 |accessdate=2013-10-12}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.sanspo.com/geino/news/20131011/akb13101120520001-n1.html |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131015115949/http://www.sanspo.com/geino/news/20131011/akb13101120520001-n1.html|archivedate=2013-10-15|script-title=ja:\uff33\uff2e\uff28\uff14\uff18\u516c\u6f14\u306b\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u3068\u9234\u6728\u307e\u308a\u3084\u304c\u521d\u767b\u5834 |language=Japanese |publisher=sanspo.com |date=2013-10-12 |accessdate=2016-08-15}}</ref> and China.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ent.sina.com.cn/y/2013-10-12/12164022621.shtml |title=SNH48\u7559\u5b66\u751f\u5bab\u6cfd\u4e0e\u94c3\u6728\u767b\u573a \u6cea\u6d12\u5267\u9662 |language=Chinese |publisher=Sina.com |date=2013-10-12 |accessdate=2013-10-12}}</ref> Her endeavors as a Japanese idol in a Chinese environment made the Japanese [[Ministry of Education, Culture, Sports, Science and Technology]] name Miyazawa a representative for the \"Tobitate! Ryugaku Japan\"-campaign (\"Take off! Study abroad!\").<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2030241/full/ |title=SNH\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u3001\u8a00\u8449\u306e\u58c1\"\u30c1\u30e3\u30ec\u30f3\u30b8\u7cbe\u795e\"\u3067\u30ab\u30d0\u30fc |language=Japanese |publisher=oricon.co.jp |date=2013-10-29 |accessdate=2014-02-26}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mext.go.jp/ryugaku/event.html |title=\u300c\u30c8\u30d3\u30bf\u30c6\uff01\u7559\u5b66JAPAN\u300d\u8a18\u8005\u767a\u8868\u4f1a |language=Japanese |publisher=MEXT |date=2013-10-29 |accessdate=2014-01-30}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2013, during the annual \"Request Hour\" concerts held by all Japanese AKB48 acts, the Miyazawa-led song \"Kiseki wa Mani Awanai\" ranked second in fan voting.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.akb48.co.jp/request_hour/2013/result.php |title=AKB48\u516c\u5f0f\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8 &#124; AKB48 \u30ea\u30af\u30a8\u30b9\u30c8\u30a2\u30ef\u30fc \u30bb\u30c3\u30c8\u30ea\u30b9\u30c8\u30d9\u30b9\u30c8100 2013 \u7d50\u679c\u767a\u8868 |publisher=Akb48.co.jp |date= |language=Japanese |accessdate=2013-09-30}}</ref>\nFollowing this, Miyazawa promoted AKB48's 30th single \"[[So Long (AKB48 song)|So Long!]]\" in TV broadcasts, even though she did not participate in the actual single recording.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://miyazawafamily-jp.blogspot.jp/2013/03/31.html |title=\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u5fdc\u63f4\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8: 3/1 \u300c\u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30b8\u30c3\u30af\u30b9\u30c6\u30fc\u30b7\u30e7\u30f3\u300d |publisher=Miyazawafamily-jp.blogspot.jp |date=2013-03-31 |accessdate=2013-09-25}}</ref> In March 2013, Miyazawa started a Twitter account, but this was suspended when it gathered too many followers on the first day; her Twitter was reopened two days later.<ref>{{cite web |author=\u30a6\u30ec\u3074\u3042 2013\u5e74 Spring (2013\u5e745\u6708\u53f7) |url=http://www.j-cast.com/tv/2013/03/22170792.html |title=SNH48\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u300c\u30c4\u30a4\u30c3\u30bf\u30fc\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u3067\u3054\u3056\u3044\u307e\u3059\u300d\u30d5\u30a9\u30ed\u30fc\u3057\u3059\u304e\u30a2\u30ab\u30a6\u30f3\u30c8\u51cd\u7d50 : J-CAST\u30c6\u30ec\u30d3\u30a6\u30a9\u30c3\u30c1 |publisher=J-cast.com |date=2013-08-19 |accessdate=2013-09-25}}</ref> Meanwhile, Miyazawa took part in AKB48's 31st single \"[[Sayonara Crawl]]\".<ref>{{cite web |first=Tommy |last=Kono |url=http://www.akb48wrapup.com/2013/04/center-for-akb48-31st-single-sayonara-crawl-unveiled/3/ |title=Center for AKB48 31st Single \"Sayonara Crawl\" unveiled! \u2022 AKB48WrapUp |publisher=Akb48wrapup.com |date=2013-04-28 |accessdate=2013-09-25}}</ref>\n\nDuring the AKB48 Group ''Rinji Sokai'' concert in [[Nippon Budokan]] in April 2013, AKB48 announced her return to Team K and concurrent membership with SNH48.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.akb48wrapup.com/2013/04/live-updates-akb48-rinji-soukai-budokan-day-4-setlist/ |title=AKB48 Rinji Soukai Budokan Concert Series 2103 \u2013 Day 4 (Night) Set List & Pictures \u2022 AKB48WrapUp |publisher=Akb48wrapup.com |date= |accessdate=2013-09-25}}</ref> In the 2013 AKB48 general election, she finished tenth overall. During the election results event, she declared her plans to focus on SNH48,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.rbbtoday.com/article/2013/06/11/108968.html |title=\u300c\u8ab0\u304b\u76ee\u3092\u899a\u307e\u3057\u3066\u3084\u308b\u3079\u304d\u3058\u3083\u306a\u3044\u306e\u304b\uff1f\u300d\u2026\u2026\u5c0f\u6797\u3088\u3057\u306e\u308a\u304c\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u3092\u5fc3\u914d |publisher=Rbb Today |date= |accessdate=2013-09-25}}</ref> and after confirmation with AKB48 management, became the first AKB48 member to voluntarily drop concurrency.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ameblo.jp/akihabara48/entry-11559488970.html |title=\u5bae\u6fa4\u4eba\u4e8b\u7570\u52d5\u306b\u95a2\u3057\u3066\u306e\u304a\u77e5\u3089\u305b\uff5cAKB48 Official Blog \u301c\uff11\uff18\uff13\uff10\uff4d\u304b\u3089\uff5e powered by \u30a2\u30e1\u30d6\u30ed |language=Japanese |publisher=Ameblo.jp |date=2013-06-24 |accessdate=2013-09-25}}</ref> As a result, she did not participate in the rock-paper-scissors tournament in 2013<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ameblo.jp/akihabara48/entry-11560697468.html |title=\u7b2c4\u56de\u3058\u3083\u3093\u3051\u3093\u5927\u4f1a\u306e\u8a73\u7d30\u306b\u3064\u3044\u3066\uff5cAKB48 Official Blog \u301c\uff11\uff18\uff13\uff10\uff4d\u304b\u3089\uff5e powered by \u30a2\u30e1\u30d6\u30ed |publisher=Ameblo.jp |date=2013-06-26 |accessdate=2013-09-25}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author=2013\u5e7406\u670824\u65e5 13\u664246\u5206 |url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/music/2025931/ |title=\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u3001AKB\u517c\u4efb\u6b63\u5f0f\u89e3\u9664 SNH48\u5c02\u4efb\u306b\u623b\u308a\u300c\u59cb\u307e\u308a\u3058\u3083\u30fc\uff01\u300d (\uff21\uff2b\uff22\uff14\uff18) \u30cb\u30e5\u30fc\u30b9-ORICON STYLE |publisher=Oricon.co.jp |date= |accessdate=2013-09-25}}</ref> and rarely appeared with the group until February 2014, when AKB48 announced Miyazawa's transfer to Nagoya-based [[SKE48]] at the Grand Reformation Festival, while staying a concurrent member of [[SNH48]].<ref name=\"akb48grandreformation\">{{cite web |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140224125430/http://www.akb48.co.jp/page/daisokaku/list.php?after=1&group=akb48 |archivedate=2014-02-24 |url=http://www.akb48.co.jp/page/daisokaku/list.php?after=1&group=akb48 |title=AKB48\u516c\u5f0f\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8\uff5cAKB48\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u5927\u7d44\u95a3\u796d\u308a (AKB48 Official Site \u2013 AKB48 Group Grand Reformation Festival Results) |language=Japanese |work=AKB48 Official Website |accessdate=February 25, 2014}}</ref> She was appointed the 'leader' of SKE48's Team S. This time, she accepted the new position after learning of the transfer via a live phone call from that event.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cinematoday.jp/page/N0060843|script-title=ja:SNH48\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u3001SKE48\u517c\u4efb\u6c7a\u5b9a\u306b\u300c\u307e\u3060\u30c6\u30f3\u30d1\u3063\u3066\u308b\u300d |accessdate=2015-06-08 |publisher=Cinematoday Inc. |language=Japanese}}</ref> However, she suffered a significant decrease in popularity in the process, as she lost over 21000 votes compared to 2013 in the 2014 AKB48 general election, but still managed to maintain the 12th position overall.<ref name=\"Shiso\">{{cite web |author=Shiso |url=http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2014/06/akb48-37th-single-senbatsu-general-election-results |title=AKB48 37th Single Senbatsu General Election Results! |publisher=tokyohive.com |date=2014-06-07 |accessdate=2014-07-03}}</ref> In SKE48, Miyazawa appeared frequently as one of the leading members in commercial campaigns, TV and stage performances, and had since then been selected to appear in AKB48's 38th single,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://natalie.mu/music/news/126355 |title=\u6e21\u8fba\u7f8e\u512a\u7d00\u3001AKB48\u65b0\u3058\u3083\u3093\u3051\u3093\u5973\u738b\u306b\u6c7a\u5b9a |publisher=natalie.com |date=2014-09-17 |accessdate=2014-09-17}}</ref> her first regular single appearance since [[Sayonara Crawl]], and her 29th title track performance overall. In the general election for the 41st single in 2015, she recovered from the heavy loss in 2014, by adding 31,000 votes to her result and ranking in at the 8th position, her personal best. Before the event, she stated that she would not be participating in future fan elections.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.daily.co.jp/newsflash/gossip/2015/06/06/0008099070.shtml |title=\u5927\u4e2d\u5c0f \u3000\u6587\u5b57\u30b5\u30a4\u30ba\uff33\uff2e\uff28\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u3000\u76ee\u6a19\u9054\u6210\u904e\u53bb\u6700\u9ad8\uff18\u4f4d |publisher=daily.co.jp |date=2015-06-06 |accessdate=2015-06-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2053932/full/?ref_cd=tw |title=\u3010\u7b2c7\u56deAKB\u7dcf\u9078\u6319\u3011\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u304c\u81ea\u5df1\u6700\u9ad8\u306e8\u4f4d 7\u5e74\u9023\u7d9a\u306e\u9078\u629c\u5165\u308a |publisher=oricon.co.jp |date=2015-06-06 |accessdate=2015-06-09}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/akb48/news/1488556.html |title=\uff33\uff2e\uff28\u5bae\u6ca2\u4f50\u6c5f\u3001\u904e\u53bb\u6700\u9ad8\uff18\u4f4d\u300c\u58c1\u7834\u308b\u3053\u3068\u3067\u304d\u305f\u300d |publisher=nikkansports.com |date=2015-06-06 |accessdate=2015-06-09}}</ref> By the end of 2015, she had appeared in 32 single A-sides of AKB48, trailing only five other members. [[Kuchibiru ni Be My Baby]], AKB48's 10th anniversary single, marked her return to the main selection of promoting members of AKB48 releases. It was her first appearance in a management selected conventional line up of 16 members since [[Give Me Five!]] in 2012, before her transfer to SNH48.\n\n===2016: Departure from 48 Group===\nDuring the nationwide broadcast of the music show \"FNS\", Miyazawa announced her departure from SKE48 and SNH48 at an undefined date in 2016.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2063993/full/  |title=\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u3001\u5352\u696d\u306e\u6642\u671f\u306f\u300c\u4eca\u300d \u300c\u65b0\u3057\u3044\u81ea\u5206\u3068\u6226\u3046\u300d\u3068\u6c7a\u610f   |publisher=Oricon |date=2016-12-16 |accessdate=2016-04-08}}</ref> She is the second member to announce her so-called \"graduation\" from the group on national TV, after [[Oshima Yuko]] on [[K\u014dhaku Uta Gassen]] in 2014. Following this, the Miyazawa-centered song \"Kiseki wa Mani Awanai\" was voted into the first place in the 2016 edition of the Request Hour concert series. During this event, a two-day concert at [[Nippon Gaishi Hall]] dedicated to her farewell was announced.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://mantan-web.jp/2016/01/24/20160124dog00m200024000c.html |title=AKB48\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\uff1a\u30ea\u30af\u30a2\u30ef1\u4f4d\u306f\u300c\u5947\u8de1\u306f\u9593\u306b\u5408\u308f\u306a\u3044\u300d\u3000\u5352\u696d\u306e\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u300c\u5fc3\u304b\u3089\u3046\u308c\u3057\u3044\u300d |publisher=mantan-web.jp |date=2016-01-24 |accessdate=2016-01-24}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2065817/full/ |title=\"\u5352\u696d\u795d\"\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u30bb\u30f3\u30bf\u30fc\u66f2\u304c1\u4f4d \u5352\u30b3\u30f3\u65e5\u7a0b\u3082\u767a\u8868\u3010\u30ea\u30af\u30a2\u30ef20\u21921\u4f4d\u3011  |publisher=oricon.co.jp |date=2016-01-24 |accessdate=2016-01-24}}</ref> She eventually left the group  in March 2016, after farewell performances in the theaters of all three groups she was affiliated with (SNH48,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ent.qq.com//a/20160317/028029.htm#p=1 |title=SNH48\u5bab\u6cfd\u4f50\u6c5f\u6bd5\u4e1a\u516c\u6f14 \u5168\u4f53\u6210\u5458\u6e29\u60c5\u9001\u522b |publisher=qq.com |date=2016-03-17 |accessdate=2016-04-08}}</ref> SKE48,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.tvlife.jp/2016/03/31/59699 |title=\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u300c\u6094\u3044\u306f\u3072\u3068\u3064\u3082\u3042\u308a\u307e\u305b\u3093\u300dSKE48\u5287\u5834\u3067\u6700\u5f8c\u306e\u5287\u5834\u516c\u6f14 |publisher=TV Life|date=2016-03-31 |accessdate=2016-04-08}}</ref> AKB48<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2069549/full/  |title=\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u3001AKB\u5f8c\u8f29\u306b\u611b\u306e\u30b2\u30ad\u300c\u5b8c\u5168\u306b\u8272\u3092\u5909\u3048\u308b\u3079\u304d\u300d  |publisher=Oricon |date=2016-04-02 |accessdate=2016-04-08}}</ref>).\n\n==Solo activities and acting career==\nAs a member of the [[AKB48 Group|AKB48 group]], Miyazawa has been promoted in many of AKB48's own shows, but also frequently appeared in Japanese radio and TV. She has published two photobooks; one in 2009 titled \"Kanojo\" and one in 2015 titled \"Namida no Yukue\". Occasionally, she was cast as an actress for feature films, stage plays and [[Japanese television dramas|Japanese TV dramas]]. In January 2014, Miyazawa was selected to play a major role in the stage play {{Nihongo|''Wings of Kuzariana''|\u30af\u30b6\u30ea\u30a2\u30fc\u30ca\u306e\u7ffc}}, the 13th volume of the [[:ja:\u5730\u7403\u30b4\u30fc\u30b8\u30e3\u30b9|Gorgeous Earth]] series, which was performed in [[Tokyo]], [[Osaka]], [[Nagoya]], and [[Fukuoka]].<ref>{{cite web |author=\u671b\u6708\u3075\u307f |url=http://www.crank-in.net/entertainment/interview/28571 |title=SNH48\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u3001\u521d\u306e\u672c\u683c\u821e\u53f0\u51fa\u6f14\u306b\u300c\u65b0\u3057\u30441\u30da\u30fc\u30b8\u304c\u958b\u304b\u308c\u308b\u300d\u300d |publisher=crank-in.net |date=2013-12-26 |accessdate=2014-01-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |author= |url=http://www.tvlife.jp/2013/12/28/15849 |title=\u5730\u7403\u30b4\u30fc\u30b8\u30e3\u30b9\u6700\u65b0\u4f5c\u300c\u30af\u30b6\u30ea\u30a2\u30fc\u30ca\u306e\u7ffc\u300d\u3067\u821e\u53f0\u521d\u6311\u6226\uff01SNH48\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u30a4\u30f3\u30bf\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\uff06\u7a3d\u53e4\u5834\u5199\u771f\u516c\u958b |publisher=tvlife.jp |date=2013-12-28 |accessdate=2014-01-30}}</ref> In July 2014, it was announced that she would play the male lead role in the stage adaption of the manga \"[[AKB49: Ren'ai Kinshi J\u014drei]]\".<ref>{{cite web |url=http://natalie.mu/comic/news/125846|script-title=ja:AKB49\u30df\u30e5\u30fc\u30b8\u30ab\u30eb\u958b\u5e55\uff01\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u3089\u304c\u71b1\u6f14 |accessdate=2015-06-08 |publisher=Natasha,Inc. |language=Japanese}}</ref> 2014 ended with her being cast in [[Nippon TV|ntv]]'s special primetime drama \"Dr. Nurse Aid\" (Dr.\u30ca\u30fc\u30b9\u30a8\u30a4\u30c9) in November.<ref>{{cite web |author= |url=http://www.ntv.co.jp/dr-nsaid/ |title=\u91d1\u66dc\u30ed\u30fc\u30c9SHOW\uff01\u7279\u5225\u30c9\u30e9\u30de\u4f01\u753b Dr.\u30ca\u30fc\u30b9\u30a8\u30a4\u30c9\uff5c\u65e5\u672c\u30c6\u30ec\u30d3 |publisher=www.ntv.co.jp |accessdate=2014-11-14}}</ref>\nIn March 2015, she performed in the gala concert celebrating the 20th anniversary of the stage play series [[:ja:\u5730\u7403\u30b4\u30fc\u30b8\u30e3\u30b9|Gorgeous Earth]], she appeared in 2013/2014.<ref>{{cite web |author= |url=http://www.chikyu-gorgeous.jp/20th_gala_concert/cast.php |publisher=chikyu gorgeous |title=Chikyu Gorgeous 20th anniversary gala concert \u2013 cast |accessdate=2015-06-09}}</ref> Some months later, it was announced that Miyazawa would perform in the stage adaptation of the popular [[sh\u014djo]] [[manga]] \"[[Crest of the Royal Family]]\" by [[Chieko Hosokawa]], scheduled for 2016. She was cast for the role of the main protagonist, sharing the role with [[:ja:\u65b0\u59bb\u8056\u5b50|Seiko Niizuma]].<ref>{{cite web |title=\u014cke no Monsh\u014d Sh\u014djo Manga Gets Stage Musical With Mamoru Miyano, SNH48/SKE48 Idol Sae Miyazawa |url=http://www.animenewsnetwork.com/news/2015-07-14/oke-no-monsho-shojo-manga-gets-stage-musical-with-mamoru-miyano-snh48-ske48-idol-sae-miyazawa/.90425 |website=Anime News Network |accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref>\nAfter finishing the play, Miyazawa collaborated with the [[cosplay]] boy group [[:ja:\u30a2\u30eb\u30b9\u30de\u30b0\u30ca (\u97f3\u697d\u30e6\u30cb\u30c3\u30c8)|ARSMAGNA]] on their single [[:ja:\u6c17\u5206\u4e0a\u3005\u2191\u2191|Kibun Joujou]], and concluded the year by scoring a main role in the [[TV Asahi]] drama {{Nihongo|''Ossan's love''|\u304a\u3063\u3055\u3093\u305a\u30e9\u30d6}}.<ref name=\"PIA Corporation\">{{cite web |url=http://www.tv-asahi.co.jp/henai/ossanslove/|script-title=ja:[86\u56de]\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u3001SP\u30c9\u30e9\u30de\u300eDr.\u30ca\u30fc\u30b9\u30a8\u30a4\u30c9\u300f\u306b\u51fa\u6f14!\u300c\u79c1\u304c\u3053\u306e1\u5e74\u3067\u611f\u3058\u305f\u300eLOVE\u3058\u3083\u306a\u304f\u3066\u201c\u3084\u3055\u3057\u3055\u3067\u3001\u3067\u304d\u3066\u3044\u304f\u611b\u201d\u300f\u304c\u4f1d\u308f\u308b\u30c9\u30e9\u30de\u300d |accessdate=2015-06-08 |publisher=PIA Corporation |language=Japanese}}</ref> She also appeared in a number of TV variety programs, for example [[:ja:\u30d2\u30eb\u30ca\u30f3\u30c7\u30b9!|Hirunandesu!]] and [[:ja:\u30ed\u30fc\u30ab\u30eb\u8def\u7dda\u30d0\u30b9\u4e57\u308a\u7d99\u304e\u306e\u65c5|R\u00f4karu rosen basu noritsugi no tabi]].\nIn July 2018, Miyazawa terminated her contract with Flave Entertainment, and signed to media agency [[Horipro]] Entertainment a year later. Inbetween she was on a hiatus from entertainment. As of 2019, Miyazawa has become a regular musical actress, having appeared nation wide in a number of successful stage plays, with her most recent signing as a double cast with accomplished Japanese singer [[May J.]] in the japanese run of [[West Side Story]].<ref>{{cite web |title=J-Pop Singer May J. Will Make Acting Debut in Tokyo's 'West Side Story' |url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/news/international/8532211/japan-may-j-acting-tokyo-west-side-story-Anita |website=Billbpard-com |accessdate=6 October 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Reception==\nMiyazawa, who is often called \"Sae-chan\" (\u3055\u3048\u3061\u3083\u3093) by fans and media,<ref>{{cite web |url=http://ure.pia.co.jp/category/miyazawa_sae |title=SNH48\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u300c\u3055\u3048\u3061\u3083\u3093\u3068\u5b66\u3076\u4e2d\u56fd\u5165\u9580\u300d-\u30df\u30e9\u30af\u30eb\u2606\u30c1\u30e3\u30a4\u30ca\u2606\u30c9\u30ea\u30fc\u30e0- |language=Japanese |publisher=Ure.Pia.co.jp |date=2013-10-12 |accessdate=2013-10-12}}</ref> belonged to the most popular members of the 48 group family with consistent high finishes in audience polls. In the AKB48 general elections, in which the lineup (called \"senbatsu\") for a given single is decided by fan voting, she placed 14th (2009), 9th (2010), 11th (2011), 11th (2012), 10th (2013), 12th(2014), and 8th (2015), respectively, which gave her a spot on the related title tracks. She is one of five members to make it to the senbatsu ranks in the first seven elections. Miyazawa and [[Sayaka Akimoto]] were frequently referred to as the \"Twin Towers\" of Team K, because of their comparably tall height and their key roles in that team. Another nickname she bears is \"Genking\"<ref>{{cite web |title=\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u3001\u4f53\u8abf\u4e0d\u826f\u3092\u660e\u304b\u3059\u300c\u672c\u5f53\u306b\u3054\u3081\u3093\u306a\u3055\u3044\u300d |url=https://mdpr.jp/news/detail/1511746 |publisher=Model Press Japan |date=15 August 2012 |accessdate=8 February 2017}}</ref><ref name=\"NPN\">{{cite web |title=AKB48 \"\u30b2\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\" \u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u304c\u30c0\u30a6\u30f3 |url=http://npn.co.jp/article/detail/72318849/ |publisher=NPN |date=17 April 2012 |accessdate=8 February 2017}}</ref> (from Japanese \"genki\" = energetic, cheerful), as she is often portrayed as loud, impulsive and energetic.<ref name=\"ReferenceA\">The Official Senbatsu Sousenkyo Guidebook 2011 - \u300cAKB\u7dcf\u9078\u6319\u516c\u5f0f\u30ac\u30a4\u30c9\u30d6\u30c3\u30af2011\u300d\uff08\u8b1b\u8ac7\u793e\uff09</ref> She is also known as AKB48's \"handsome idol\" (Japanese: \"ikemen idol\") due to her [[tomboy]]ish mannerisms and image.<ref name=\"NPN\"/><ref name=\"ReferenceA\" /> Accordingly, she was named as the idol best suited to act male roles and stereotypes in a 2017 survey among college students.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u30a2\u30a4\u30c9\u30eb\u597d\u304d\u5973\u5b50\u5927\u751f\u304c\u9078\u3093\u3060\u3001\u301d\u751f\u301f\u30a2\u30a4\u30c9\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\uff01\uff01 |url=https://hustlepress.co.jp/20170304_column/ |publisher=Hustle Press |accessdate=4 March 2017}}</ref> Among members of the AKB48 groups, a disproportionately high fraction of her fan following is female.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u9078\u6319\u306b\u5f37\u3044 \"SKE\"\u306f\u30db\u30f3\u30c8!?\uff5e\u30d3\u30c3\u30b0\u30c7\u30fc\u30bf\u3067\u8aad\u3080\u300cAKB\u7dcf\u9078\u6319\u300d\uff5e |url=http://docs.yahoo.co.jp/info/bigdata/special/2015/03/ |publisher=yahoo Japan |accessdate=25 October 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |title=\uff33\uff2b\uff25\u5bae\u6fa4\u4f50\u6c5f\u3000\u5352\u696d\u3067\u300c\u5973\u6027\u30d5\u30a1\u30f3\u58ca\u6ec5\u300d\uff1f |url=http://www.tokyo-sports.co.jp/entame/entertainment/525483/ |publisher=Tokyo sports |accessdate=8 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nIn the animated series [[AKB0048]], the character [[AKB0048#Sae Miyazawa the 10th|Miyazawa Sae The 10th / Asamiya Youko]] is modeled after her, voiced by [[Mai Nakahara]].\n\n== Discography==\n\n=== AKB48===\n\n==== Main singles ====\n<!---- When filling in her roles as Center, please specify a reliable media source that credits her as such. An implied position in a video or album does not mean she is the center [[WP:OR]]. Some singles do not have centers. ---->\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! data-sort-type=\"number\" | No. <!--- AKB48 major single number ---->\n! style=\"width:150px;\"| Title <!--- title of main single ---->\n! Role<ref name=\"entame\">Center and A-side lineup information provided by {{cite web |url=http://entamedata.web.fc2.com/music2/akb48single.html |title=AKB48 \u6b74\u4ee3\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u9078\u629c\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc\uff082006\u5e74\uff5e2013\u5e74\uff09  |trans-title=(2006\u20132013) AKB48 successive single member selection |work=entamedata.web.fc2.com |accessdate=2013-09-23}}</ref>  